    "summary": "Peter de Ruiter\nExecutive C-level/Non Executive/MD NABC/PwC Senior Tax Partner.\n\nPeter has a strong affiliation and broad experience with International Business (NL, EU, Africa). In any organisation he will optimise the People, Finance, Tax and Legal functions. Visionary leader who defines clear and convincing strategies with his teams and ensures effective implementation.\n\nWith regard to Africa, Peter is convinced that the private sector plays a crucial role in the economic and sustainable development of the Continent. Peter is involved in the work of the Netherlands-African Business Council as Senior Counsel for many years.  From 2017- 2021 he was NABC\u2019s Managing Director.\n\nPrior to this Peter built up over 30 years of professional experience as Partner in PwC and EY. He worked and lived in a number of countries and gained international business expertise in emerging and developing markets such as Central Eastern Europe, Nigeria and West-Africa.\n\nPeter is a trained international tax lawyer with a passion for the technical aspects of global and regional trade and transnational investment projects. \n\nHe built up an outstanding track record of successful high-profile client engagements, always with the focus on achieving the business objectives of his clients. \n\nAs Senior Partner in PwC, Peter has led larger (300+ professional staff) teams operating in a number of different jurisdictions. Over the years he has achieved impressive revenue and profit growth with his teams in these countries.\n\nMyers-Briggs Type Indicator: INTJ.",
